On July 16, 2009, Vice President Biden will travel to the Richmond, VA area to highlight the progress of the Recovery Act at J. Sargeant Reynolds Community College. The Vice President will discuss how the Recovery Act is building a 21st-century economy in the Richmond area and across the nation. The event is open to the press, but media must RSVP by July 15. The event details include the location, press entrance, parking, camera pre-set, restricted access, press arrival, final press access, event start time, cable run, and throw distance. Media credentials are required to be worn at all times during the event. For logistical questions, Samantha Finke can be contacted at 202.757.9079.